<br>
I hadn't played DAOC till last night because my machine didn't meet the minimum requirements.  Finally, I decided to take the plunge hoping that I could just get in.  The results so far:<br>
<br>
I've been able to play with my vintage machine:<br>
Pentium II 333MHz, 192 MB RAM, 32 MB VRAM.  <br>
<br>
The gameplay has been ok except for some choppiness when using the arrow keys to control direction.  It is a bit hard to adjust direction because the computer seems to not respond quickly enough, and one tends to go too far left or right when using the arrow keys.  Using mouselook works better, but I just prefer to use the arrow keys.  Anyhow, other than that glitch, everything else seems fine thus far.  Fighting hasn't been a problem.  Played last night for a few hours, and leveled a couple of characters to lvl 3 without any problems due to lag etc.  However, I should note that I was playing late ... after 10 pm PST, so only about 500 people were on the server.<br>
<br>
Not that I would recommend continuing to play with such an old machine (I've got a new system on the way myself), but if someone hasn't tried DAOC yet because of the specifications on the box, you can certainly get into the game and try it out with a system below the minimum requirement.<br>
<br>
See you in game.<br>
<br>
Karna<br>
Druid of Quellious <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubroomhilda.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Broomhilda</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/30/01 7:16:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=152.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ....</span><hr size=1> What kinda video card are ya using?  I tried with a P2 300, 128mb RAM, Voodoo3, and i couldnt see the labels at the info screen where you put your name and other info down.  I'm thinking it was my video card though.  Oh, and this machine ran EQ, UO, AO, and Pool of Radiance fine.<br>
<br>
Anyways, I had to upgrade at some point, DAoC just made the decision alot easier. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukarnathedruid.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Karna the druid</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/30/01 7:33:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=152.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: FYI: DAOC with Older Computers</span><hr size=1> I had trouble with the labels at the info screen as well (I should have mentioned that), but I managed to input the data with some guesswork.<br>
<br>
IIRC, my video card is a Diamond Stealth (Don't have the exact specs here at work). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utandaina.showPublicProfile?language=EN>tandaina</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/31/01 7:42:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=152.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: FYI: DAOC with Older Computers</span><hr size=1> I've got an OLD card: Diamond Viper 770 Ultra.  Love that thing. ;)  It runs DAoC flawlessly.  I've heard folks having trouble with Voodoos though. <p>Silverleaf Goldenthorn<BR>
Warden of Connla
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ueqkaldail.showPublicProfile?language=EN>EQ Kaldail</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/31/01 9:20:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=152.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Older computer</span><hr size=1> I'm playing in an Athlon 850 that has a Viper V770 in it, and it runs just fine.  Little bit of video choppiness, but I blame the extraordinarly low-end video card for that 100%.<br>
<br>
I just wish I could figure out why my 1.4ghz machine is so crashy so I could play on my good machine. :(<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udasteel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dasteel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/31/01 11:23:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=152.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Older computer</span><hr size=1> The labels being off is usually caused by having large fonts selected. One of the few things that Mythic screwed up ;) <p><i>It seemed like a good idea at the time ...</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umistwalk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>mistwalk</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://mistwalk.homestead.com/index.html" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/31/01 4:09:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=152.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Older computer</span><hr size=1> Im running P2 500, Voodoo2, of all things, 256 memory, and not a very fast hard drive....with few problems at all. Just in Camelot during rush hour, and when storming the Hiberian gates (200 peeps dyin, castin, flailin around....you  get the picture) .......and actually, originally started with 126 memory, just added more thinkin it would help in the cities(it didnt). <br>
<br>
So yah, for all you who were worried bout the voodoo thing....dont, heh....tho Verant says they do NOT support voodoo cards, they have a video option to choose just that before you enter the game, so...Im sure there are problems they know bout that I just havent run across yet, but other than the cloak graphics being, um, not quite what I know they should look like, lol, it is running just peachy, considering. We all know we'll upgrade soon enough, just give it a shot, chances are you'll be just fine for quite a while.<br>
<br>
An add here....I play on Percival, a VERY crowded server most of the time, and my problems in Camelot disappear entirely when its NOT very busy, so....draw your own conclusions ;)<br>
