<br>
Bring up display properties (from the control panel, or by right-clicking on your desktop and choosing 'properties')<br>
<br>
Choose the 'Appearance' tab<br>
<br>
Under 'Scheme', choose 'Windows Standard'<br>
<br>
Hit OK<br>
<br>
<br>
There may be minor differences in the procedure for different OSs (Win98 vs WinME, etc.)<br>
Note that this will change all the fonts and colors for Windows interface elements to the default. You'll have to change stuff back if you don't like the look.<br>
<br>
